cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with LTE Device-to-device (D2D) network and proposes a method to enhance spectral efficiency. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses maximizing the reuse of radio resources in the LTE network, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system-level solution to improve spectral efficiency in the LTE network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions HD video as one of the next-generation wireless applications, which falls under the multimedia category. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss security, the proposed method of utilizing neighboring BS spectrum may have implications for security and interference management, which falls under the cryptography and security category.
